<TD BGCOLOR="#ffffff" ALIGN="center" VALIGN="top" WIDTH="100%"><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3">
<B>BLACK BUTTERFLY PRESS</B></FONT>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE ALIGN="center" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="80%">
<FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><Font size="1">
<block><b>Welcome</b>
 to Black Butterfly Press, the home of Maxine Thompson's Literary Services, and Thompson's Literary Agency.  Dr. Maxine Thompson, a retired social worker with 23 years of experience, became an editor in 1998. Since that time, she has edited/ghostwritten over 1,000 books, many which have made the best seller's list, including the New York Times Best Seller list. In 2003, her literary agency grew out of her God-given calling. She represents national Best Selling Authors, Michelle McGriff, Ph.D., and Shelia Goss, who both have respectively received 15 and 11 contracts in three years.<p>

Dr. Thompson is also an author of 14 titles. <a href="http://www.poweroflearning.com/chapter.cfm?chapterid=273"><b>Excerpt</b></a> On 7-8-06, SECRET LOVERS hit the bestseller's list on Black Expressions Book Club. On 10-20-07, SECRET LOVERS made #87 on Amazon.com's bestseller's list under Romance Contemporary Anthologies (Please see what Readers think under the Acknowledgments Link.) Anthology, NEVER KNEW LOVE LIKE THIS BEFORE, has made top 100 bestsellers on Amazon as #13 under multicultural anthologies, and #47 under Romance categories. <p>
You can order Maxine Thompson's latest novel, Hostage of Lies as of 12-1-09. It has also been picked up by Black Expressions' Book Club .<p></p>
<p></p>Hostage of Lies by Maxine Thompson was voted as one of the Best Books of 2009 on Black Pearls Magazine<p></p>
<a href="http://edcmagazine.blogspot.com/2009/12/best-books-of-2009-our-relationships.html">Black Pearl Magazine</a><p></p>
Please check out Dr. Thompson's  urban thriller, LA Blues, which was released 07-01-11 to rave reviews. LA Blues II was released May 29, 2012. LA Blues III was released on August 2013. Pick up a copy of Van T. Womack's book, The Miraculous Power of Massage, released by Black Butterfly Press. <p>Monday nights join Dr. Thompson's Internet Radio Show on Artistfirst.com at 9:00 p.m. EST where she promotes other writers, indie or traditionally published. As of 3/4/2011, Dr. Thompson celebrated 9 years of being a host on Internet radio, talking about the Publishing Industry, promoting indie writers, New York Times Bestselling Authors, and promoting ebooks. She also has blog tours and book reviews on her alternate site, http://www.maxinethompsonbooks.com.
<p>Black Butterfly Press also has an ebook store that you might want to visit. You can sign up for her free newsletter. You can join her on twitter, Facebook, and Linkedin.  I hope you enjoy your stay!!!
</block>
<p>
Thank you,<p>

